    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review Drink/Drug driving laws and sentencing for offenders.",
        "additional_details": "Current sentences for causing death or serious injury whilst over the prescribed limit are unfairly lenient.\r\n \r\nMultiple convictions for over the prescribed limit should carry a lifetime driving ban.\r\n\r\nFailure to provide a specimen - This is currently an easier option to hide the amount of alcohol in a persons\u2019 system. It\u2019s loophole which often results in a more lenient disqualification as intoxication levels cannot be established, this should be a mandatory 5 year disqualification.",
        "background": "Recently a man was sentenced to just 4 years in prison for killing a mother of 4 whilst over the prescribed limit for both alcohol and cocaine. \r\n\r\nThe offender in this instance had already served a disqualification for being over the limits.",
